Sat down and finished the game in one try. Looked at my achievements to see I collected only about 1/3 of them. Time to go back! Although, I found quite a few secret room/levers, maps, but don't know how they all tie together in the end? I must have missed something? 
Anyway, glad I played it ;)

Also, did not have any issues whatsoever on my iPhone 4S. Zero crashes.

If you set out playing this game with hopes of finding some 'secret' in Bryce Manor - this is not your game. Secrets relating to the manor will need to be found elsewhere, as they are most definitely not here. I was looking for secrets. I was a spy, weaving webs and getting those gross bugs out of my face while I was attempting to crack the code. All of a sudden - oh my glob - the hornets must be bosons because they pass straight through my webs! I actually find tackling the hornets more fun than the rest of the game. Check out the Hornet Smash game they made as a promotion for this game. Hella fun.
